<blockquote>
<strong>How to use it:</strong> Work through each section with your leadership team. Don't try to do this alone — the V/TO only works when the people who will be held accountable to it have had a say in building it. Give yourself two to three hours for the first pass, and expect to revisit it.
</blockquote>

<hr />

<h2>Why the Template Is Just the Starting Point</h2>

<p>Here's what we've seen happen when leadership teams try to fill in the V/TO on their own, without facilitation:</p>

<ul>
    <li>The owner writes it themselves and hands it to the team to "agree with"</li>
    <li>The team fills it in but avoids the hard conversations — especially around accountability and priorities</li>
    <li>Everyone nods along, nothing changes, and the document sits in a drawer</li>
    <li>Two people have fundamentally different ideas about what the business is actually for — and nobody says it out loud</li>
</ul>

<p>The document itself is not the hard part. <strong>The conversations are the hard part.</strong></p>

<p>When is your 10-Year Target realistic versus delusional? When do your Core Values actually mean something versus being words on a wall? What happens when two co-owners have a different 3-Year Picture in their heads and have never compared notes? What do you do when the Issues List has 40 things on it and you're not sure which three actually matter most?</p>

<p>These are not template questions. They're facilitation questions — and they require someone in the room who's not emotionally invested in the outcome.</p>

<h3>What a Facilitated V/TO Session Looks Like</h3>

<p>A Tradewise facilitated V/TO session typically runs as a full-day offsite with the business owner and their key leadership team (usually two to five people). A Tradewise advisor leads the session using the EOS process, ensuring:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Every person in the room has a genuine voice — not just the owner</li>
    <li>The hard disagreements get surfaced and resolved, not papered over</li>
    <li>Each section is stress-tested: is this real, is it measurable, does everyone mean the same thing?</li>
    <li>You leave with a completed V/TO that the whole team is genuinely bought in to</li>
    <li>Rocks are assigned with clear owners before anyone leaves the room</li>
    <li>You have a 90-day check-in booked so accountability doesn't evaporate the next morning</li>
</ul>

<p>The difference between a V/TO that gathers dust and a V/TO that actually changes how a business runs almost always comes down to whether the leadership team built it together, under proper facilitation.</p>

<h3>This Is the Gap Tradewise Fills</h3>

<p>Most advisors will hand you a framework and tell you to run the sessions yourself. Most business coaches will lead the session but don't know the trade industry well enough to pressure-test your numbers or challenge your assumptions with real benchmarks.</p>

<p>Tradewise advisors work exclusively with trade businesses. We know what a realistic 3-Year Picture looks like for a $3M plumbing business in South-East Queensland. We know which Issues come up again and again, and which ones are symptoms versus root causes. We know how to have the conversation between a business owner and their second-in-command that clarifies whether they're actually aligned — or just being polite.</p>

<p>The template gives you the structure. The facilitated session gives you the alignment. That alignment is what turns a plan into a business that doesn't depend entirely on you.</p>

<hr />

<h2>Next Step</h2>

<p>Download the template, work through it with your team, and see what surfaces. Then, if you want someone in the room who's done this before — someone who can hold the space, challenge the assumptions, and make sure you leave with something real — book a free call with a Tradewise advisor.</p>

<p>The first conversation costs you nothing. A business without direction costs you everything.</p>

